            Trident armed warrior sage
            %br
            Clad in tiger hide,
            %br
            Face covered with ascetic's mark,
            %br
            Adoring the third eye.
            %br

            %br
            Smoking weed in high blue mountain
            %br
            Where no soul does survive,
            %br
            A jet black snake around his neck
            %br
            Of pulsating blue light.
            %br

            %br
            Wilder mane of thick black hair
            %br
            Wound in matt at top,
            %br
            Streaming down this very crown
            %br
            A river tamed in dreaded lock.
            %br

            %br
            An immortal sage of timeless descent
            %br
            Ageless body don't weather at all,
            %br
            Since beginning he meditates in silence
            %br
            In darkness, he waits for the call.
            %br

            %br
            When Evil rise in epic proportions
            %br
            When Righteous fight for wrong,
            %br
            When nature's temper is at its peak
            %br
            And the list of Wars is long.
            %br

            %br
            Then cries the mighty bull
            %br
            His verdict, A sad song,
            %br
            Tears in his eyes the sage rises
            %br
            Weaves a spell too strong.
            %br

            %br
            First the air thrums with sound of fire
            %br
            Following the divine beat,
            %br
            Then begins the Dance of Death
            %br
            As the Earth quakes under his feet.
            %br

            %br
            The Third Eye unfolds, as the dance begins
            %br
            Engulfs the world in its majestic flame,
            %br
            Mountains melt and Ocean rises,
            %br
            Playing its part in his conspired game.
            %br

            %br
            When all is done and none are left
            %br
            Then ends this lamenting song,
            %br
            The Earth is peaceful and quiet again
            %br
            Ready once more to be born.
